net.objectzoo.ebc.join

Class GenericJoin<Input1,Input2,Output>

  • java.lang.Object

        • net.objectzoo.ebc.join.Join<Input1,Input2,Output>
          • net.objectzoo.ebc.join.GenericJoin<Input1,Input2,Output>
  • Type Parameters:
    Input1 - the type of input one of this Join
    Input2 - the type of input two of this Join
    Output - the type of output of this Join
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SendsResult<Output>

    public abstract class GenericJoin<Input1,Input2,Output>
extends Join<Input1,Input2,Output>
    This Join base class joins two input values to an output value that has a constructor taking the two input values as parameters. The class implements the boilerplate code required to provide two input actions and a result event as well as trace logging of value input and send results. The Join waits for every input to be set at least once before creating a result event. Once both inputs have been set an output is created and sent. After that there are two different modes of operation depending on the resetAfterResultEvent parameter setting. If resetAfterResultEvent is set to true (which is the default) then after each result event the two input values are reset and the procedure to wait for both inputs starts from the beginning. If resetAfterResultEvent is set to false then for each following single input invocation a new output is created and sent until the Join is manually reset again. If reset the procedure to wait for both inputs starts from the beginning. To manually reset the Join the Join.resetAction() can be invoked. To use this Join create a (possibly anonymous) subclass that specifies concrete type parameters.
    Author:
    tilmann
